    "testimony": [
        [
            "KHINTANA MBEKWA",
            "(sworn states)",
            "Unknown"
        ],
        [
            "REV XUNDU",
            "How are you related to Sibunu?",
            "Unknown"
        ],
        [
            "KHINTANA MBEKWA",
            "My grandmother.  I have come to talk about Mbekwa.",
            "Male"
        ],
        [
            "REV XUNDU",
            "He also was one of the victims of the Nonqulana incident at Bizana.  Is that so?",
            "Unknown"
        ],
        [
            "KHINTANA MBEKWA",
            "Yes.",
            "Male"
        ],
        [
            "REV XUNDU",
            "What happened?  Was he detained?",
            "Unknown"
        ],
        [
            "KHINTANA MBEKWA",
            "Yes he was detained.",
            "Male"
        ],
        [
            "REV XUNDU",
            "Where?",
            "Unknown"
        ],
        [
            "KHINTANA MBEKWA",
            "A lot of places, Bizana, Lusikisiki.",
            "Male"
        ],
        [
            "REV XUNDU",
            "When was he released?",
            "Unknown"
        ],
        [
            "KHINTANA MBEKWA",
            "He was detained for two years, released in the third year.",
            "Male"
        ],
        [
            "REV XUNDU",
            "How was he health wise?",
            "Unknown"
        ],
        [
            "KHINTANA MBEKWA",
            "He was ill of health.  He would tell us how he was ill treated.  He said that they were beaten up all the time.  They were accused of not respecting the Government.  He was very thin when he was released.  Blind as well.",
            "Male"
        ],
        [
            "REV XUNDU",
            "And his arm?",
            "Unknown"
        ],
        [
            "KHINTANA MBEKWA",
            "He said that he had been hit with the back of a gun and he could not use his right arm, therefore his health just deteriorated.  And it deteriorated until such time that he died.  He could not work even on his plantations, because he had no strength.",
            "Male"
        ],
        [
            "REV XUNDU",
            "And his cattle, his livestock?",
            "Unknown"
        ],
        [
            "KHINTANA MBEKWA",
            "The people who worked together with the Government they destroyed his livestock.  They poisoned his cattle.",
            "Male"
        ],
        [
            "REV XUNDU",
            "What is your request to the Commission?",
            "Unknown"
        ],
        [
            "KHINTANA MBEKWA",
            "I request that the Commission give me a bit of money so that I can solve problems that emanated from this incident.",
            "Male"
        ],
        [
            "REV XUNDU",
            "You also requested that your roads be fixed up.  I have got a list of requests here.",
            "Unknown"
        ],
        [
            "KHINTANA MBEKWA",
            "Yes those are my requests.",
            "Male"
        ],
        [
            "REV XUNDU",
            "What is your clan name?",
            "Unknown"
        ],
        [
            "KHINTANA MBEKWA",
            "Gadebe.",
            "Male"
        ],
        [
            "REV XUNDU",
            "You have also requested that we build a tombstone.",
            "Unknown"
        ],
        [
            "KHINTANA MBEKWA",
            "Yes it would be good, because some of my people died.  I could request that as well.",
            "Male"
        ],
        [
            "REV XUNDU",
            "Anything else?",
            "Unknown"
        ],
        [
            "KHINTANA MBEKWA",
            "No.   Thank you.  Maybe I will give the other a chance.",
            "Male"
        ],
        [
            "REV XUNDU",
            "Thank you Tlobi.",
            "Unknown"
        ],
        [
            "KHINTANA MBEKWA",
            "You are a very kind man.",
            "Male"
        ]
    ]
